365
00:23:34,270 --> 00:23:34,920
Okay.

366
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:42,290
[I. Video analysis]

367
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:04,720
Fellow prosecutors.

368
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:08,030
This is the video footage of the incident
provided by the witness.

369
00:24:08,030 --> 00:24:10,030
Regarding Jiang Ting's case
of killing her husband,

370
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:12,120
I'd like all to share your opinions.

371
00:24:12,550 --> 00:24:13,240
That night,

372
00:24:13,310 --> 00:24:14,810
when Zhang Yuan broke into
Jiang Ting's home,

373
00:24:14,810 --> 00:24:16,030
he was carrying a knife.

374
00:24:16,030 --> 00:24:18,350
Jiang Ting was facing
a serious threat to her life.

375
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:20,420
Therefore, I still maintain
it was justifiable defense.

376
00:24:20,420 --> 00:24:22,330
A key criterion for justifiable defense

377
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:24,770
is the immediacy of the unlawful threat.

378
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,830
When Jiang Ting stabbed Zhang Yuan
for the first time,

379
00:24:27,830 --> 00:24:30,160
he had already lost his ability to attack,

380
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:32,270
and her crisis was already over.

381
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:34,270
However, she continued

382
00:24:34,270 --> 00:24:36,400
and stabbed Zhang Yuan six more times.

383
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:37,790
Therefore, I believe

384
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:38,860
these six stabs

385
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,060
can definitely be classified
as intentional assault.

386
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,350
Last night,

387
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:46,550
we collected the subjective descriptions

388
00:24:46,550 --> 00:24:47,680
of the same video footage

389
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:49,400
from five groups of third parties.

390
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,590
Please take a look.

391
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:54,520
Group one said

392
00:24:54,570 --> 00:24:56,200
Jiang Ting stabbed Zhang Yuan
viciously with a knife.

393
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:56,830
[Jiang Ting is suspected of intentional homicide]
[Video Evidence Analysis Report]

394
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:57,830
After he fell down,

395
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:59,200
she continued stabbing him ferociously

396
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,400
six times in a row.

397
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,000
Group two said

398
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,430
Zhang Yuan held a knife

399
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,920
and cornered Jiang Ting on the balcony.

400
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,000
Jiang Ting was terrified

401
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:10,270
and seemed to have closed her eyes.

402
00:25:10,270 --> 00:25:12,070
She then stabbed Zhang Yuan.

403
00:25:12,070 --> 00:25:13,640
After seven stabs, she opened her eyes.

404
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:14,680
Different people

405
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,290
have different biases.

406
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,600
We always talk about being objective,

407
00:25:19,110 --> 00:25:20,590
but how many people

408
00:25:20,590 --> 00:25:22,440
can be absolutely objective?

409
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:25,400
I've read the latest interrogation
transcript.

410
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,200
It shows Jiang Ting has admitted

411
00:25:27,830 --> 00:25:30,230
that if Zhang Yuan dared to come to her home,

412
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,510
even killing him

413
00:25:31,740 --> 00:25:33,590
would count as justifiable defense.

414
00:25:33,590 --> 00:25:35,120
Doesn't this further prove

415
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:36,900
she had the intention to kill?

416
00:25:37,210 --> 00:25:39,240
And she did buy a new knife.

417
00:25:40,550 --> 00:25:43,240
This does fit the criteria for
crime preparation.

418
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,590
But remember,

419
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,480
before the incident,

420
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:48,270
Jiang Ting was receiving nearly twenty calls

421
00:25:48,270 --> 00:25:49,750
from Zhang Yuan every day.

422
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:51,070
Nearly twenty calls

423
00:25:51,070 --> 00:25:53,510
every day for several months.

424
00:25:53,750 --> 00:25:54,830
In other words,

425
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,920
Jiang Ting was living in constant fear

426
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:59,400
that Zhang Yuan might appear at
any moment.

427
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,790
So isn't it possible that the knife

428
00:26:00,790 --> 00:26:02,310
was for her self-defense?

429
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,400
We need to consider

430
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:06,030
what kind of situation

431
00:26:06,030 --> 00:26:08,880
would make Jiang Ting feel she needed
a knife for protection.

432
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,420
We always emphasize whether
an action is justifiable defense

433
00:26:11,420 --> 00:26:14,100
depends on the immediacy
of the unlawful threat.

434
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:16,190
If the unlawful threat hasn't come

435
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,830
but is very imminent,

436
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:18,940
can one fight back?

437
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,030
Or if

438
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:21,840
the unlawful threat has ended

439
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,240
but the danger still exists,

440
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,440
can one fight back?

441
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:25,830
In such cases,

442
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,960
there should be another criterion
for judgment,

443
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,690
which is the last opportunity.

444
00:26:30,070 --> 00:26:32,310
What if a criminal points a gun at you

445
00:26:32,350 --> 00:26:33,110
what would you do?

446
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:33,880
Run!

447
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,290
Can you outrun a bullet?

448
00:26:35,350 --> 00:26:36,880
Then we can only wait to die.

449
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:37,930
You have a knife.

450
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:39,400
Then use it to defend yourself.

451
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,750
When do you pull out the knife?

452
00:26:40,750 --> 00:26:41,590
If we strictly follow

453
00:26:41,590 --> 00:26:43,160
the standard of ongoing threat,

454
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,510
then we would have to wait until

455
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:46,110
the criminal aims before we can
defend ourselves.

456
00:26:46,110 --> 00:26:47,200
Then we'll die too.

457
00:26:47,510 --> 00:26:48,160
Therefore,

458
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,110
the moment the criminal pulls out a gun

459
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:52,270
is the victim's last chance
for self-defense.

460
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:53,200
If it's too late,

461
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,200
they could lose their life.

462
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,440
But was it Jiang Ting's last chance?

463
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,500
Then one stab would have been enough.

464
00:27:00,270 --> 00:27:01,000
Everyone.

465
00:27:02,510 --> 00:27:03,590
A woman

466
00:27:04,310 --> 00:27:06,790
was beaten by a man for five whole years.

467
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:09,010
Have you ever thought about

468
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:12,590
what kind of fear this woman lived in?

469
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,310
If we had been Jiang Ting,

470
00:27:14,950 --> 00:27:17,050
and that man suddenly appeared again,

471
00:27:17,050 --> 00:27:18,440
threatening to hurt me,

472
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:20,110
and I happened to have a knife nearby,

473
00:27:20,110 --> 00:27:20,920
how would we fight back?

474
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:21,750
You dare to take a knife!

475
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:22,550
Stay back!

476
00:27:22,820 --> 00:27:24,150
Prosecutor Xu just said

477
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:27,240
that perhaps one stab
would have been enough.

478
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,790
You may have overlooked the extreme
nature of the situation.

479
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:31,840
In such an extreme situation,

480
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,590
if we had been Jiang Ting,

481
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:35,030
after I stabbed Zhang Yuan once...

482
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:36,310
I'll kill you!

483
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,070
How could I be certain

484
00:27:38,070 --> 00:27:40,440
that the man who is much stronger than me,

485
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:41,400
would fall down

486
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,480
and lose his ability to fight back?

487
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,440
Wouldn't he, out of rage,

488
00:27:45,510 --> 00:27:46,590
continue to assault me,

489
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:48,550
and beat me to death?

490
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,350
Can we expect

491
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:55,590
Jiang Ting

492
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:57,350
to stop and calmly consider

493
00:27:57,350 --> 00:27:58,790
whether everything she was doing

494
00:27:58,790 --> 00:27:59,550
met

495
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:01,750
the criteria for justifiable defense?

496
00:28:02,030 --> 00:28:03,050
We can't, can we?

497
00:28:06,590 --> 00:28:08,400
All of us are sitting here now,

498
00:28:08,830 --> 00:28:10,640
objective and calm,

499
00:28:10,790 --> 00:28:11,750
drinking tea,

500
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,350
and watching this brief video.

501
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,150
But shouldn't we also

502
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:19,480
try to see things from Jiang Ting's
perspective?

503
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,830
If I had been Jiang Ting,

504
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:24,970
putting myself in the defendant's shoes,

505
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:28,520
and these few minutes

506
00:28:30,590 --> 00:28:32,240
were my last chance

507
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,560
to escape from unlawful harm,

508
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:35,010
I must fight back.

509
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,960
We can't demand that a victim

510
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,720
be a perfect victim.

511
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:39,920
Accordingly, we can't

512
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,640
demand that a justifiable defense

513
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:44,070
be a perfect defense.

514
00:29:01,490 --> 00:29:03,010
I want to remind everyone

515
00:29:04,830 --> 00:29:06,400
that as prosecutors,

516
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:10,310
when we handle all kinds of crimes,

517
00:29:10,350 --> 00:29:12,650
we can't just focus on the law itself

518
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:14,530
and ignore the people

519
00:29:15,350 --> 00:29:16,590
in these cases.

520
00:29:20,940 --> 00:29:21,590
Because

521
00:29:22,490 --> 00:29:24,360
we're not handling cases,

522
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,070
but people's lives.

523
00:29:28,310 --> 00:29:29,030
Because

524
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:30,880
the law

525
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,740
must not yield to wrongdoing.

526
00:29:49,260 --> 00:29:50,050
Therefore,

527
00:29:51,830 --> 00:29:53,090
for Jiang Ting's case,

528
00:29:53,690 --> 00:29:55,920
I think her action constitutes
justifiable defense,

529
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:58,120
and prosecution should not be pursued.

